org.ndnx.ndn.impl.sync
Class SyncTreeEntry

java.lang.Object
  org.ndnx.ndn.impl.sync.SyncTreeEntry

public class SyncTreeEntry
extends Object

Entry used for navigating trees of hashes. It also does the work of saving and retrieving node data from the common node cache. But these objects can not be shared across comparators because they contain data about where the comparator is in a treewalk. The policy about how to save nodes is: If the node came from the network, it can be retrieved via a request so we use a SoftReference to allow these to be garbage collected when necessary. If the node is local, we built it so can't be guaranteed that we know how to rebuild it if we lose it. So we hold onto these directly here, and remove them explicitly when no longer needed in the higher level code.

getNode

public SyncNodeComposite getNode(XMLDecoder decoder)
Decodes the hash if not yet done. Note that this should not be called from a handler (unless we already know the node is decoded) because decoding is long and expensive and could stall the netmanager thread. We allow a separate decoder because nodes typically contain more elements than are usually allowed by default by the standard decoder. We can speed things up by preallocating more space.
